'''Aleksandar Pavlović''' ({{lang-sr-Cyrl|Александар Павловић}}; born 3 May 2004) is a German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]]. He is known for his passing accuracy, vision and composure on the ball.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2026-05-16-aleksandar-pavlovic-leads-europe-with-passing-accuracy-this-season|title=Aleksandar Pavlovic leads Europe with passing accuracy this season|date=16 May 2026|website=Tribuna.com|access-date=16 May 2026}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Youth career===
Pavlović was an [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|academy of Bayern Munich]] youth product. He joined Bayern Munich in 2011 when he was seven years old from [[SC Fürstenfeldbruck]].<ref name="auto"/> On 23 July 2021, Pavlović extended his contract until 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bavarianfootballworks.com/2021/7/23/22589849/bayern-munich-transfer-news-rumors-extend-contracts-youth-players-aydin-eberhart-pavlovic-reinelt|title=Bayern Munich extend contracts of four youth players, send one out on loan|first=Phillip|last=Quinn|date=23 July 2021|website=Bavarian Football Works|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref> On 3 May 2022, he signed a contract with Bayern Munich until 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/2022/05/fc-bayern-verlangert-mit-talente-trio-jonathans-pavlovic-und-dibrani-bleiben|title=FC Bayern verlängert mit Talente-Trio: Jonathans, Pavlovic und Dibrani bleiben | language = de |date=3 May 2022|website=Sport1|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref> That same month, he started training with the [[FC Bayern Munich|senior squad of Bayern Munich]] for the first time, subsequently appearing on the bench for a pair of [[Bundesliga]] matches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportbild.bild.de/bundesliga/vereine/bayern-muenchen/fc-bayern-top-talent-aleksandar-pavlovic-begeistert-thomas-tuchel-im-training-83774564.sport.html|title=FC Bayern: Top-Talent Aleksandar Pavlovic begeistert Thomas Tuchel im Training | language = de |date=2 May 2023|website=[[Bild]]|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref>

===Senior career===
Pavlović played for the senior Bayern Munich in the pre-season in the summer of 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportal.blic.rs/fudbal/reprezentacija-srbije/aleksandar-pavlovic-biser-bajerna-igrace-za-srbiju-gledao-ga-i-piksijev-pomocnik/2023073008341586900|title=Biser Bajerna igraće za Srbiju! Piksijev pomoćnik otkrio novu pobedu nad Nemačkom|website=Sportal|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref> He made his [[Bundesliga]] debut as a substitute in an 8–0 victory against [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]] on 28 October 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportal.blic.rs/fudbal/medjunarodni-fudbal/bundesliga/bajern-pobedio-sa-80-hari-kejn-dao-gol-sa-pola-terena-neverovatan-mec-bundeslige-na-alijanc-areni/2023102815264179961|title=Nestvarne scene u Minhenu! Kejn ga dao sa pola, igralo se deset na devet, a Bavarci su brojali do osam: O ovom meču Bajerna će se pričati /VIDEO/|website=Sportal | language = sr | date = 28 October 2023 | access-date = 1 November 2023}}</ref> On 1 November 2023, he signed a professional contract with Bayern Munich until 2027.<ref>{{cite magazine| url = https://www.kicker.de/doppelte-premiere-pavlovic-erhaelt-profivertrag-bei-bayern-976783/artikel | title = Doppelte Premiere: Pavlovic erhält Profivertrag bei Bayern | language = de |magazine= [[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] | date = 1 November 2023 | access-date = 1 November 2023}}</ref> On 4 November, he provided his first assist in Bundesliga to the third goal scored by [[Harry Kane]] in a 4–0 away victory against [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/profis/bundesliga/2023-2024/borussia-dortmund-fc-bayern-muenchen-04-11-2023/spielbericht |title=Starke Bayern triumphieren im Klassiker beim BVB |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |language=de |date=4 November 2023 }}</ref> One week later, Pavlović made his first start in a 4–2 victory against [[1. FC Heidenheim]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/11/five-special-stories-from-the-heidenheim-clash |title=Five special stories from the Heidenheim match |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=11 November 2023 }}</ref> On 29 November, he made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut, coming off the bench in the 64th minute in a goalless draw against [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/champions-league/2023-2024/fc-bayern-muenchen-fc-kopenhagen-29-11-2023/report |title=Bayern held by Copenhagen |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=29 November 2023 }}</ref> On 27 January 2024, he scored his first goal in a Bundesliga 3–2 away victory against [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-au/football/bundesliga/articles/bayern-munich-edge-thrilling-clash-with-augsburg-to-maintain-title-pressure-2024-01-27|url-status=dead|title=Bayern Munich edge thrilling clash with Augsburg to maintain title pressure|website=[[BeIN Sports]]|publisher=BeIN Media Group|date=27 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127171140/https://www.beinsports.com/en-au/football/bundesliga/articles/bayern-munich-edge-thrilling-clash-with-augsburg-to-maintain-title-pressure-2024-01-27|archive-date=27 January 2024}}</ref> Later that year, on 16 June, Pavlović extended his contract until 2029.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2024/06/fc-bayern-extend-contract-with-aleksandar-pavlovi%C4%87-until-2029 |title=FC Bayern extend contract with Aleksandar Pavlović |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=16 June 2024 }}</ref>

In the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|2024–25 season]], he achieved his first Bundesliga title with the club.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kovbasa |first=Ivan |url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/dreams-come-true-seven-years-ago-aleksandar-pavlovic-watched/ |title=Dreams come true: Seven years ago, Aleksandar Pavlovic watched Bayern's title win - now he's champion himself |publisher=Tribuna.com |date=16 May 2025 }}</ref> On 15 April 2026, he scored his first Champions League goal in a 4–3 win over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Ramsay |first=George |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/bayern-munich-vs-real-madrid-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/0a9rKBvUokd8/YoaRQ1kID6pi/ |title=Pavlovic's first Champions League goal |publisher=The New York Times |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Germany to a [[Serbs|Serbian]] father and a [[Germans|German]] mother,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://onefootball.com/en/news/debutant-aleksandar-pavlovic-discusses-maiden-germany-nomination-39204475 | title = Debutant Aleksandar Pavlović discusses maiden Germany nomination | website = Onefootball | date = 11 March 2024 | access-date = 28 June 2025 | first = Daniel | last = Pinder}}</ref><ref name="Soccerway profile">{{soccerway|aleksandar-pavlovic/671281|accessdate=31 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Aleksandar Pavlović: Who is Bayern Munich's homegrown midfield master? |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/aleksandar-pavlovic-who-is-bayern-munich-s-homegrown-midfielder-germany-serbia-25235 |access-date=5 June 2025|website=Bundesliga}}</ref> Pavlović holds dual citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nogomania.com/article/Bayern-Munich-coach-Thomas-Tuchel-considers-promoting-Serbian-talent-Aleksandar-Pavlovic-to-first-team|title=Bayern Munich coach Thomas Tuchel considers promoting Serbian talent Aleksandar Pavlović to first team|website=Nogomania|date=28 August 2023|access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref> In September 2021, he was called up to the [[Serbia national under-18 football team|Serbia U18]] for a set of friendly matches.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://fss.rs/u18-mladji-omladinci-imaju-dve-provere-u-sloveniji/ | script-title = sr:U18 {{!}} Млађи Омладинци Имају Две Провере У Словенији|publisher=[[Football Association of Serbia]]| language = sr | date = 13 September 2021 | access-date=24 October 2023}}</ref> In November 2023, Pavlović was called up to the [[Germany national under-20 football team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sport.de/news/ne5818898/fc-bayern-fcb-juwel-fuer-nationalmannschaft-nominiert/|title=Bayern-Juwel für Nationalmannschaft nominiert|website=sport.de|date=10 November 2023|access-date=5 June 2025}}</ref>

On 14 March 2024, Pavlović was called up for the [[Germany national football team|German senior squad]] by head coach [[Julian Nagelsmann]] for the friendly matches against [[France national football team|France]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web |date=14 March 2024 |title=Start ins EM-Jahr mit sechs Neulingen und sechs Rückkehrern |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402201335/https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/ |archive-date=2 April 2024 |access-date=14 March 2024 |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |language=de}}</ref> However, he missed both fixtures due to suffering from [[tonsillitis]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/pavlovic-to-miss-games-against-france-and-the-netherlands-259761/|url-status=dead|title=Pavlovic to miss games against France and the Netherlands |publisher=German Football Association |date=19 March 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240319233245/https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/pavlovic-to-miss-games-against-france-and-the-netherlands-259761/|archive-date=19 March 2024}}</ref>

Pavlović was selected in the German preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.br.de/nachrichten/sport/aleksandar-pavlovic-vom-fc-bayern-steht-im-em-kader,UCde1Z3 | title = Aleksandar Pavlovic vom FC Bayern steht im EM-Kader | language = de | website=[[BR24]]|date=13 May 2024 | access-date=14 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-kader-fuer-heim-em-bekannt-261479/|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt kader für heim-em bekannt|date=16 May 2024|publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date=16 May 2024|language=de }}</ref> He made his senior debut on 3 June in a friendly match against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rnd.de/sport/deutschland-ukraine-die-einzelkritik-der-dfb-elf-im-ueberblick-FSJBWFPFJJBV7GLCQ7K2REIUX4.html |title=Kein Tor gegen die Ukraine: Vier Zweien, aber auch eine Fünf für DFB-Stars|publisher=[[RedaktionsNetzwerk Deutschland]]|language=de |date=3 June 2024 }}</ref> Pavlović was confirmed in Germany's final 26-man squad,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list|title=UEFA Euro 2024: All squads and players full list|date=7 June 2024|access-date=5 June 2025|website=Olympics Committee}}</ref> but had to withdraw due to an illness.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/pavlovic-verpasst-em-can-nachnominiert-262267/|title=Pavlovic verpasst EM – Can nachnominiert|publisher=German Football Association|date=12 June 2024|access-date=5 June 2025|language=de}}</ref> On 7 September 2024, he scored his first goal for Germany in a 5–0 victory against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] during the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/en/germany-hammer-hungary-5-0-in-nations-league-match/a-70162964 |title=Germany hammer Hungary 5-0 in Nations League |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]|date=7 September 2024 }}</ref>

On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

